  in /usr/lib/libgio-2.0.so.0\n    ffi_call_unix64 (/usr/src/debug/libffi/libffi-3.5.2/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/../src/x86/unix64.S:104)\n      in /usr/lib/libffi.so.8\n    ffi_call_int (/usr/src/debug/libffi/libffi-3.5.2/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/../src/x86/ffi64.c:676)\n      in /usr/lib/libffi.so.8\n    ffi_call\n      in /usr/lib/libffi.so.8\n    pygi_invoke_c_callable (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/python3.14/site-packages/gi/_gi.cpython-314-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\n    _function_info_vectorcall (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/python3.14/site-packages/gi/_gi.cpython-314-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\n    _PyEval_EvalFrameDefault\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    _PyEval_Vector (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    PyEval_EvalCode\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    run_mod.lto_priv.0 (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    pyrun_file.lto_priv.0 (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    _PyRun_SimpleFileObject (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    _PyRun_AnyFileObject (:?)\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    Py_RunMain\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    Py_BytesMain\n      in /usr/lib/libpython3.14.so.1.0\n    __libc_start_call_main (/usr/src/debug/glibc/glibc/csu/../sysdeps/nptl/libc_start_call_main.h:58)\n      in /usr/lib/libc.so.6\n    __libc_start_main\n      in /usr/lib/libc.so.6\n```\n\n</details>\n\n\nAnyway, this is hard for me to understand, except that the leak generally has something to do with dbus. I'm currently trying [memray](https://bloomberg.github.io/memray), which seems to have support for combined python & native stack traces, but it will be a while until I see the results.\n\nHmm, tray is fairly simple and pretty much only listens to org.blueman.Applet with one or more dbus proxies. Which blueman version are you running this on?\nReproduced on both 2.4.6-2 from the Arch Linux repos, and on 202152648b4942dd536d7e60b89a356d5a344861 when running from source with `PATH=\"$PWD/apps:$PATH\" BLUEMAN_SOURCE=1 ./apps/blueman-applet`\nmy mistake, I'm not sure where I got \"blueman-tray\". Looking at my shell history, I've been looking at \"blueman-applet\" this whole time.\nmemray looks and works really nice for me. It has a nice live tui when run with `--live`.\n\nI noticed this just now, what the hell pulseaudio plugin \ud83d\udc40 .\n<img width=\"1332\" height=\"129\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/130feaa2-d173-4cac-9be3-a4c388b1c4c0\" />\nLooks like that pulseaudio space [isn't supposed to take up real memory, just virtual memory](https://man.archlinux.org/man/extra/libpulse/pulse-client.conf.5.en#shm_size_bytes=). But in practice it does seem to be using real memory:\n\n```\n\u276f grep '65536' -A 24 /proc/$(pgrep blueman-tray)/smaps\nSize:              65536 kB\nKernelPageSize:        4 kB\nMMUPageSize:           4 kB\nRss:               39764 kB\nPss:               39764 kB\nPss_Dirty:         39716 kB\nShared_Clean:          0 kB\nShared_Dirty:          0 kB\nPrivate_Clean:        48 kB\nPrivate_Dirty:     39716 kB\nReferenced:        35036 kB\nAnonymous:         39764 kB\nKSM:                   0 kB\nLazyFree:              0 kB\nAnonHugePages:         0 kB\nShmemPmdMapped:        0 kB\nFilePmdMapped:         0 kB\nShared_Hugetlb:        0 kB\nPrivate_Hugetlb:       0 kB\nSwap:              25772 kB\nSwapPss:           25772 kB\nLocked:                0 kB\nTHPeligible:           1\nProtectionKey:         0\nVmFlags: rd wr mr mw me ac sd\n```\n\nCould be worth making a bug report about, although personally I don't care since my OS can move it to swap if I have memory pressure.\n\n---\n\nAnyway, my latest trace doesn't seem to have given me useful results. When observed, blueman-applet is doing fine, and blueman-tray is acting up:\n\n<img width=\"955\" height=\"77\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/adf9c934-79d9-4d03-a2fb-89b5f14db078\" />\n\nI did discover that memray [has a live attach/detach mode](https://bloomberg.github.io/memray/attach.html), so I've done that and will see the results over the next while:\n\n```\npython3 -m memray attach 1684264 --verbose --native --compress-on-exit --output memray-1684264.out\n```\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/blueman-project/blueman/commit/e82be790895a1de6a1cce8d4039f317fc36e6fde"], "created_at": "2026-03-03T03:01:10Z"}
{"repo": "blueman-project/blueman", "pull_number": 3173, "instance_id": "blueman-project__blueman-3173", "issue_numbers": [3171], "base_commit": "d073ab4b153bb06d355d31007ba358114ef83a74", "patch": "diff --git a/blueman/main/Applet.py b/blueman/main/Applet.py\nindex a709ace24..cdd91548f 100644\n--- a/blueman/main/Applet.py\n+++ b/blueman/main/Applet.py\n@@ -1,7 +1,3 @@\n-import gi\n-gi.require_version(\"Gtk\", \"3.0\")\n-\n-from gi.repository import Gio, GLib, Gtk\n import logging\n import signal\n from typing import Any, cast\n@@ -21,6 +17,14 @@\n from blueman.plugins.applet.StandardItems import StandardItems\n from blueman.plugins.applet.StatusIcon import StatusIcon\n \n+import gi\n+gi.require_version(\"Gtk\", \"3.0\")\n+gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")\n+\n+from gi.repository import Gio\n+from gi.repository import GLib\n+from gi.repository import Gtk\n+\n \n class BluemanApplet(Gtk.Application):\n     def __init__(self) -> None:\ndiff --git a/blueman/main/Manager.py b/blueman/main/Manager.py\nindex 4e1213851..6e0413da8 100644\n--- a/blueman/main/Manager.py\n+++ b/blueman/main/Manager.py\n@@ -31,7 +31,11 @@\n import gi\n gi.require_version(\"Gtk\", \"3.0\")\n gi.require_version(\"Gdk\", \"3.0\")\n-from gi.repository import Gtk, Gio, Gdk, GLib\n+gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")\n+from gi.repository import Gtk\n+from gi.repository import Gio\n+from gi.repository import Gdk\n+from gi.repository import GLib\n \n \n class Blueman(Gtk.Application):\ndiff --git a/blueman/main/Services.py b/blueman/main/Services.py\nindex b2e0bb3ab..58e265fb1 100644\n--- a/blueman/main/Services.py\n+++ b/blueman/main/Services.py\n@@ -11,6 +11,7 @@\n \n import gi\n gi.require_version(\"Gtk\", \"3.0\")\n+gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")\n from gi.repository import Gtk\n from gi.repository import GLib\n from gi.repository import Gio\ndiff --git a/blueman/main/Tray.py b/blueman/main/Tray.py\nindex e7e85ed85..374f02e45 100644\n--- a/blueman/main/Tray.py\n+++ b/blueman/main/Tray.py\n@@ -5,10 +5,13 @@\n import sys\n from blueman.Functions import log_system_info\n from blueman.main.DBusProxies import AppletMenuService, AppletStatusIconService\n-from gi.repository import Gio, GLib\n-\n from blueman.main.indicators.IndicatorInterface import IndicatorNotAvailable\n \n+import gi\n+gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")\n+from gi.repository import Gio\n+from gi.repository import GLib\n+\n \n class BluemanTray(Gio.Application):\n     def __init__(self) -> None:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Blueman-applet fails to start with object has no attribute error.\nBlueman-applet fails to launch with the following error:\n\n```python\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/usr/bin/blueman-applet\", line 39, in <module>\n    app = BluemanApplet()\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/site-packages/blueman/main/Applet.py\", line 34, in __init__\n    s = GLib.unix_signal_source_new(signal.SIGINT)\n        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/site-packages/gi/overrides/__init__.py\", line 31, in __getattr__\n    return getattr(self._introspection_module, name)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/site-packages/gi/module.py\", line 130, in __getattr__\n    raise AttributeError(\"%r object has no attribute %r\" % (\n                         self.__name__, name))\nAttributeError: 'gi.repository.GLib' object has no attribute 'unix_signal_source_new'\n```\n\nBlueman version: 2.4.6\nGlib version: 2.84.4\n", "hints_text": "Please include the upstream bug report if there is one (https://bugs.gentoo.org/971271).\n\n`unix_signal_source_new` is in `GlibUnix` so make sure you have the relevant introspection files. \n\nWe should probably make sure it's there with `gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")`.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Please include the upstream bug report if there is one (https://bugs.gentoo.org/971271).\n\n`unix_signal_source_new` is in `GlibUnix` so make sure you have the relevant introspection files. \n\nWe should probably make sure it's there with `gi.require_version(\"GLibUnix\", \"2.0\")`.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/blueman-project/blueman/commit/581d4727db06943b5c33a14516d092d72b1361b8"], "created_at": "2026-03-17T10:13:00Z"}
